EXPERIMENT-2 Search Insert Position (LEETCODE PROBLEM 2)

1) AIM:-Given a sorted array of distinct integers and a target value, return the index if the target is found. 
If not, return the index where it would be if it were inserted in order.

2) ALGORITHM:-
1- Initialize:
      A) low = 0
      B) high = nums.size() - 1
2- Repeat while low <= high:
      A) Calculate the middle index:
         mid = low + (high - low) / 2
      B) If nums[mid] == target, return mid.
      C) If nums[mid] >= target, search in the left half by setting:
         high = mid - 1.
      D) Otherwise, search in the right half by setting:
        low = mid + 1.
3- When the loop ends, the target is not present in the array.
4- Return low, because low represents the correct position where the target should be inserted while keeping the array sorted.

3) CODE:-
class Solution {
public:
    int searchInsert(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.size() - 1;

        while (low <= high) {
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            if (nums[mid] == target) {
                return mid;
            }
            else if (nums[mid] >= target) {
                high = mid - 1;
            }
            else {
                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return low;
    }
};
